<FIRST>r i PM-Germany-Escape     04-10 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Germany-Escape,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>Border Guards Thwart Escape Attempt by East German Men</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto BER1,4,5,6</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communist border guards opened fire as two East
German men attempted to flee over the Berlin Wall to the West
during the weekend, police said.
   The West Berlin police said the men were arrested and led away
from the border fortifications after the escape was thwarted.
   The men did not appear to have been injured, police said.
   ADN, East Germany's state news agency, acknowledged the
incident, but called it ``an act organized and ordered from West
Berlin.''
   ADN said a warning shot was fired by a border guard to prevent
the men from ``illegally crossing the frontier.''
   The four Allied powers in West Berlin condemned the use of force
at the Berlin Wall, calling it a ``serious violation of basic human
rights.''
   East German border troops have used deadly force at least three
times in recent weeks to prevent people escaping over the wall that
divides the city.
</TEXT>
