<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Man Kills One Arab, Wounds Two Others</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Updates with one Arab killed, at least two wounded. No Pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man opened fire tonight with an Israeli-made
Uzi submachine gun, killing one Arab and wounding two others near
the Jaffa Gate of the Old Walled City of Jerusalem, according to
police and hospital reports.
   Israel Army Radio said some reports from witnesses indicated the
gunman may have been wearing a uniform. It said the assailant ran
into the nearby Mamilla quarter, a deserted area of abandoned
buildings scheduled for demolition.
   Police blocked off the area and began a search.
   The shooting took place about 7:45 p.m. at the Jaffa Gate, one
of the main entrances to the Old Walled City.
   The radio identified the dead man as Mohammed Shawish, a
resident of the Old Walled City.
   Officials at Bikur Holim Hospital said another Arab, identified
as Mahmoud Tarek, 19, of Jerusalem was in critical condition with
wounds to the stomach and head. A third man, Mohammed Awash, was
being treated for at least three bullet wounds to the arms and legs.
