Monday with Secretary of State James A. Baker III to discuss ways
of resolving the crisis in Lebanon.
   Dumas, emerging from the two-hour meeting, said Lebanon was on
their agenda but declined to elaborate. ``We are studying
possibilities for installing peace in the region,'' he told
