<FIRST>u i AM-Brazil-Prison     04-10 0270</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Brazil-Prison,0279</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Storm Prison, Free Hostages; At Least Eight People Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police stormed a prison in central
Brazil on Monday with guns blazing and rescued about 150 hostages
at a cost of at least eight lives _ six convicts and two policemen,
an official reported.
   Moacir Mendes dos Santos a spokesman with the state secretary
for public security, said all hostages were freed, but he was not
sure if any were badly injured in the shooting at Carumbe Prison in
Cuiaba, 1,380 miles northwest of Rio de Janeiro.
   Dos Santos said the 250 mutinous inmates were armed with knives,
clubs and revolvers taken from guards who were overpowered at the
same time the hostages were seized Sunday afternoon near the end of
visiting hours.
   At least 20 policemen and prisoners were hurt, he said by phone.
   He said about 300 heavily armed officers ``entered firing after
negotiations failed.''
   He said most of those being held were relatives of prisoners,
including a small number of children, as well as several guards.
   The prisoners demanded revolvers, machine guns, a bus to the
airport, and a plane to fly them to an undisclosed destination, dos
Santos said.
   According to press reports, which dos Santos could not confirm,
the convicts also demanded that a priest and a nurse accompany them
to the airport.
   Non-stop negotiations went on between prison officials and
inmates until Monday afternoon, when police decided they had to
invade the penitentiary, dos Santos said.
   Dos Santos said all figures were unofficial as phone lines to
the prsion were cut Sunday by the prisoners.
</TEXT>
