<HEAD>Singer Grace Jones Held in Jamaica On Cocaine Charge</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: SUBS 2nd graf to CORRECT movie she appeared in.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINGSTON, Jamaica (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Famed singer-actress Grace Jones is in
jail after being arrested over the weekend for possession of
cocaine, police said Monday.
   They said the Jamaican-born Ms. Jones, 37, who became a movie
star playing opposite Roger Moore in the James Bond film ``A View
to a Kill,'' was taken into custody Saturday at the home of a
friend, entertainer Chris Stanley.
   A police report said ``a powdery substance believed to be
cocaine was found in her handbag. It was wrapped in two Jamaican $2
currency notes.''
   The police did not say precisely how much cocaine was found.
   The arrest was made in the Kingston suburb of Stony Hill, where
Ms. Jones was vacationing. She was being held in the police lockup
there and was scheduled for hearing Tuesday at Stony Hill Resident
Magistrates Court.
   Ms. Jones lives in Los Angeles and New York.
