<FIRST>u i AM-France-Crash 3rdLd-Writethru a0748 04-10 0306</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-France-Crash, 3rd Ld-Writethru, a0748,0312</SECOND>
<HEAD>Plane Crashes in French Mountains</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with five grafs to UPDATE with officials saying all aboard
killed. Edits to trim. Pick up 7th pvs, `The control...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VALENCE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger plane lost control and
crashed into a foggy mountainside in southeastern France on Monday
night, killing all 22 people aboard, officials said.
   Rescuers located the wreckage of the Fokker 27 about 3{ hours
after the crash, which occurred shortly after 9 p.m. as the plane
was about to land, local officials said.
   They found bodies among the aircraft's scattered debris in a
forest near the village of Leoncel, about 15 miles from this city
in southeastern France.
   The wreckage was on the northern face of the Vercors mountain,
at an altitude of 3,900 feet. Officials said the cloud cover was
low and the area was foggy.
   The twin-engine turboprop, was flying for the private airline
Europe Aero-Service. It was making a regular flight from Paris'
Orly Airport to Valence.
   The control tower at Mont Verdun, near Lyon, lost contact with
the plane at 9:10 p.m. The plane was scheduled to land at 9:18 p.m.
at the Chabeuil airport, near Valence, which is south of Lyon.
   There was no immediate explanation why the aircraft flew into
the mountainside as it was making its landing approach.
   Three children were among the 19 passengers aboard, police and
rescue officials said. Three crew members were aboard the aircraft.
   Officials said rescue workers concentrated their search for the
82-foot aircraft around Leoncel because numerous residents reported
hearing a loud noise or explosion at about the same time the
aircraft lost contact with the control tower.
   A Fokker 27 crashed March 4, 1988 on a flight from Nancy to
Paris, killing 23 people. It was the worst plane accident in France
since 1981.
