<DOCNO> AP890410-0214 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-04-10-89 0223EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>a a BC-SPE--Outdoors:Adventuresforwomen     04-10 0307</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-SPE--Outdoors: Adventures for women,0311</SECOND>
<HEAD>RETRANSMITTING to insert AP logo.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>SPECIAL EDITION</BYLINE>
<HEAD>Outdoors: Adventures for women over 30 ^AP LaserPhoto NY705</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>Evanston, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Not all women of a certain age want to
spend their vacations frying on the beach or sightseeing through
the windows of an air-conditioned car.
   Some like more challenge: Riding a packhorse through Yellowstone
or the Grand Canyon, trekking through the Blue Ridge Mountains
(with a llama to carry gear), white water rafting on the Colorado,
riding a horse in Ireland or a camel in Kenya.
   Travel packager Susan Eckert started her Rainbow Adventures with
these women in mind, organizing outings they would be unlikely to
arrange on their own. She limits her tours to women over 30.
   Many women in this age group never have had an opportunity for
this kind of activity, Eckert says. ``They're also reluctant to go
with their families,'' she adds.
   Her firm made a survey of 5,000 over-30 women and discovered
that only one in six wants to travel with family. Half said they
participated in fitness and diet programs, and almost a fourth of
them earn at least $35,000 a year.
   ``This survey reveals that women are no longer happy with the
same old getaway to the beach,'' says Eckert. ``These women want to
participate in their vacations. They don't want to be passive
travelers at their stage in life.''
   Eckert, a photographer and Peace Corps veteran, sensed a good
market that tied in with her own interests when she started her
firm in l982, organizing seven tours.
   This year she's offering 16 packages, ranging from a $239
weekend canoe trip on the Wisconsin River to a $2,495 two-week
cruise of the Greek Islands. She and eight associates _ all women,
most of them with active careers _lead the tours.
</TEXT>
