<FIRST>r f AM-Britain-RollsRoyce     04-10 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Britain-Rolls Royce,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rolls-Royce Makes Offer For Northern Engineering</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rolls-Royce PLC said Monday it will acquire
Northern Engineering Industries PLC in a deal that values the
British maker of electrical generating equipment at 306 million
pounds, or about $520 million.
   The jet engines manufacturer Rolls-Royce, which already holds a
4.7 percent stake in the manufacturer, said the stock swap values
NEI at 128 pence, or $2.18 dollars, a share.
   Rolls-Royce said it will offer seven new shares for every 10 NEI
shares.
   Rolls-Royce called off discussions with NEI last year on the
possibility of a merger. At the time, Rolls-Royce said the boards
of the two companies ``have not been able to agree to terms on
which to establish further relationships.''
   The offer represents a 23 percent premium over the price of NEI
shares on last Oct. 28, the day before Rolls-Royce took its stake
in NEI, the company said.
   Rolls-Royce said it expects the merger to lead to benefits in
research and development, overseas representation, financing and
the provision of gas turbine-operated small power stations.
</TEXT>
