<FIRST>r f BC-HenleyPurchase 1stLd-Writethru   04-10 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Henley Purchase, 1st Ld-Writethru,0231</SECOND>
<HEAD>Henley Group Buys Defense Conglomerate</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 5th graf to CORRECT that $100 million was total contribution.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMPTON, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Henley Group Inc. said Monday it would buy
the 50 percent stake in PA Holdings Inc. it does not already own
for $165 million from Wasserstein, Perella &amp; Co., its partner in
the 1988 buyout of the aerospace and defense company.
   A purchase agreement was completed during the weekend, Henley
spokesman Norman Ritter said Monday. The final sale would be
completed after the Henley board gives its approval, he said.
   Henley has had operating responsibility for PA Holdings since it
teamed with Wasserstein Perella, a New York investment firm, to buy
the company from Whitman Corp. in a $1.2 billion leveraged buyout
last August.
   In a leveraged buyout, a company is bought with mostly borrowed
funds, which are then repaid from the firm's cash flow or the sale
of its assets.
   Henley and Wasserstein Perella contributed a total of $100
million to the buyout.
   PA Holdings designs and makes aircraft flight-control actuation
systems, hydrugh Cleveland Pneumatic Co., PA Holdings designs,
develops, makes and overhauls landing gear for commercial and
military aircraft.
   PA Holdings had approximately $1 billion in sales in 1988.
</TEXT>
